# Demo Builder: healthstack-patient-portal
# Status: COMPLETE (re-verified 2026-06-14, all files present and syntax-clean)

---

## What was built

### Demo (4 files, no build step)
- `michaelwegter.com/public/demos/healthstack-patient-portal/index.html`
- `michaelwegter.com/public/demos/healthstack-patient-portal/styles.css`
- `michaelwegter.com/public/demos/healthstack-patient-portal/api.js`
- `michaelwegter.com/public/demos/healthstack-patient-portal/app.js`

React 18 via `esm.sh` CDN, no bundler needed. Full working app with hash-router
state machine across 7 views.

### Views implemented
1. **Login** -- credential form with one-click-fill demo creds panel (patient + admin)
2. **Services browser** -- 4-provider card grid, Sesame-care-style with avatar initials,
   specialty, star ratings, price chips ($65-$95/visit), "Book Appointment" CTA
3. **Slot picker** -- compact time-slot grid for the selected provider; calls POST /book
4. **Checkout** -- order summary + mock Stripe card form; calls POST /checkout
5. **Confirmation** -- green checkmark, PaymentIntent ID, slot/provider/amount summary
6. **Patient dashboard** -- tabbed view: Appointments list + Health Records upload stub
7. **Admin dashboard** -- stat cards (total bookings, unique patients, audit events),
   side-by-side audit log + PHI-minimized patient roster (initials only), full bookings table

### Backend (new blueprint)
- `mw-backend/healthstack_blueprint.py` -- Flask Blueprint at `/healthstack`
  - 7 endpoints: /login, /services, /book, /checkout, /dashboard/patient,
    /dashboard/admin, /upload
  - Role-bearing JWT (patient | admin), ephemeral per-boot secret
  - `require_role(["patient"])` and `require_role(["admin"])` decorator factory
  - In-memory seeded data: 2 users, 4 providers, 1 pre-seeded booking, 5 audit events
  - Blueprint syntax verified: OK
- `mw-backend/server.py` -- blueprint registered after art_store_blueprint block

### Portfolio registry
- `michaelwegter.com/src/data/workSamples.js` -- id:6 appended
  - slug: `healthstack-patient-portal`
  - color: `#12b4c8`, icon: `🏥`, frameStyle: `baroque`
  - href resolves to `import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "demos/healthstack-patient-portal/"`

