## Hero flow (for deploy-test)

1. Load demo URL
2. Click "patient@healthstack.demo / DemoPatient123!" to fill credentials
3. Click "Sign in securely" -> lands on Patient Dashboard
4. Click "Browse providers" or switch to services view
5. Click "Book Appointment" on any provider card
6. Select a slot -> "Confirm Appointment" -> calls /book, receives booking_id
7. Checkout page shows order summary -> click "Pay $XX.00" -> calls /checkout
8. Confirmation page shows green check + PaymentIntent ID
9. "View my dashboard" -> patient dashboard shows new booking with Paid status
10. Logout -> re-login as admin@healthstack.demo
11. Admin dashboard shows total_bookings, audit log with new entries, PHI-minimized roster

---

## HIPAA/trust signals in the demo

- Header: TLS 1.3 chip (green dot)
- Stripe note: "Card data never touches our servers"
- Upload tab: "PHI minimized: only the minimum necessary information is stored"
- Admin roster: "PHI Minimized" badge, shows initials only (no full names)
- Audit log: "HIPAA-aware" badge, timestamped event trail
- Footer chips: "PHI handling follows minimum-necessary principle", "HIPAA-aware patterns", "Role-based JWT auth"

